Dan blesses us with a solid hour of stellar comedy, injecting a dark and doleful 
edge to the worlds of science, video games, and the trials of growing up 
nerdy. But don't take our word for it; listen to the pros: "This album is the 
third best resource for jokes by Dan Telfer." -Patton Oswalt "I love Dan 
Telfer. He is wonderful. He is like a goofier, smarter, funnier, taller, me with 
glasses. And male parts." -Maria Bamford "If you're one of those people who 
likes being reminded that you'll never be as funny as Dan Telfer, go ahead 
and listen to this album! I won't - it just makes me sad." -Scott Aukerman 
"Dan Telfer gave me a ride in his car once." -Doug Benson "Dan Telfer has an 
album? Of comedy? Please check it out and send me a review on the internet. 
I'm sure it's great. He's very funny, super smart and nice." -Brian Posehn 
"One time I tried to help Dan break into a cemetery. His comedy chops are 
vastly superior to his B&E skills." -Kyle Kinane "Of all the performers I've 
known over the years, Dan Telfer, more than any of them, seems the most 
compelled to do stand-up comedy. ÃƒÂ¡And I don't think it's because of some 
deep-seated need for attention, or because he's seeking love from strangers 
that was denied him as a child; I think he needs to do stand-up comedy 
because he can't be alone with his own thoughts. ÃƒÂ¡Coincidentally, he's 
hilarious." -Paul F. Tompkins
